===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} ''[[povre#Middle English|povre, povere]]'' from {{etyl|fro}} ''[[povre#Old French|povre]]'', ''[[poure#Old French|poure]]'' (Modern {{etyl|fr|-}}: ''[[pauvre]]''), from {{etyl|la}} ''[[pauper]]'' from {{etyl|OL.}} *{{term||pavo-pars|getting little}} from {{proto|Indo-European|pau-|smallness|lang=}}. Akin to {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|feaw|fēawa|lang=ang}} "little, few". Displaced native {{enm}} ''[[arm#Middle English|earm, arm]]'' "poor" (from {{ang}} ''[[earm#Old English|earm]]'' "poor"), {{etyl|enm}} ''[[wantsum#Middle English|wantsum, wantsome]]'' "poor, needy" (from {{non}} ''[[vant]]'' "deficiency, lack, want"), {{enm}} ''[[unlede#Middle English|unlede]]'' "poor" (from {{ang}} ''[[unlæde#Old English|unlǣde]]''), {{enm}} ''[[unweli#Middle English|unweli, unwely]]'' "poor, unwealthy" (from {{ang}} ''[[un-#Old English|un-]]'' +  ''[[welig#Old English|weliġ]]'' "well-to-do, prosperous, rich").

